<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[Preheat oven to 175C, lightly brush a 9 inch springform pan with olive oil.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Warm the milk and stir in the honey to dissolve. Whisk together the olive oil, orange zest, and egg yolks]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Combine the toasted pine nuts, flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl. Add to the milk mixture (2) and stir well to make a batter.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Whip the egg whites using a hand mixer to soft peaks and fold the egg whites through the batter using a spatula.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Pour half the batter into the pan, scatter with the rosemary, add the other half of the batter, and drizzle with a little olive oil.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Place the cake in the oven and bake for 30-35 minutes until the cake is set and a toothpick inserted into the centre comes out clean.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Allow to cool for 10 minutes, then turn out and cool on a rack.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Dust with icing sugar and serve with a dollop of creme fraiche.]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
